ation for iOS 15 app · pointfreeco/swift-composable-architecture · Discussion #3280\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pointfreeco/swift-composable-architecture/discussions/3280\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I found information about iOS development and TCA (The Composable Architecture), though there were no specific results for \"ggaebiz\" as a GitHub project.\n\nHere's what the search revealed:\n\n**TCA (The Composable Architecture):**\n\nThe Composable Architecture (TCA) is a library for building applications in a consistent and understandable way, with composition, testing, and ergonomics in mind. It can be used in SwiftUI, UIKit, and more, and on any Apple platform (iOS, macOS, iPadOS, visionOS, tvOS, and watchOS).\n\nTCA focuses on state management, composition and testing. It's developed by Brandon Williams and Stephen Celis from Point-Free.\n\n**Key Components:**\n\nTo build a feature using TCA you define State (a type that describes the data your feature needs), Action (a type representing all actions that can happen), and Reducer (a function describing how to evolve state given an action, including returning any effects like API requests).\n\nThe search results showed various iOS projects built with TCA, but did not return specific information about \"ggaebiz.\" If you're looking for a specific GitHub repository by that name, it may not be widely indexed or may use different keywords in its documentation.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"b3113300-b094-427f-a533-1a51ab4c954f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T08:07:09.763Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"c719bb54-b41f-4980-82a7-1b11694c12cb","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/user/Desktop/Dotton","sessionId":"8d447c48-c623-49ac-b918-9597042b694d","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"main","slug":"eventual-gathering-anchor"}
